  <bioghist id="aspace_1c069c69c5a51936a1334b8921f45fa7">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>Harold Edwards (1936-2020) was a mathematician who focused on number theory, algebra, and the history of mathematics. Alongside Bruce Chandler, Edwards co-founded <emph render="italic">The Mathematical Intelligencer</emph>. Edwards wrote expository books on specific theories and functions; textbooks on linear algebra, calculus, and number theory; and essays on constructive mathematics. He graduated from the University of Wisconsin–Madison in 1956, received an Master of Arts from Columbia University in 1957, and a Ph.D from Harvard University in 1961. He joined the faculty at New York University in 1966, and was an emeritus professor from 2002 until his death.</p>  </bioghist>
